snippet.title: When My Dad Is On Mount Rushmore (Barron Trump Singing)
snippet.description:
When My Dad Is On Mount Rushmore 

Check us out on Spotify! https://open.spotify.com/album/3y1CZVxPBVqYl2ljdNVWno?si=lLRWLYbeQcuXD9TQDeKi7A

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

Lyrics:
[Verse 1]
In the land where eagles soar,
Where freedom rings from shore to shore,
There stands a mountain, grand and tall,
Honoring leaders who gave their all.

[Verse 2]
Washington, Jefferson, Lincoln's gaze,
Roosevelt's courage in challenging days.
I dream of one more face to see,
A symbol of strength and liberty.

[Chorus]
When my dad is on Mount Rushmore,
His legacy forevermore.
Carved in stone, for all to see,
A testament to our country's legacy.
Through trials faced and battles won,
His story joins the timeless ones.
When my dad is on Mount Rushmore,
America's spirit will endure.

[Verse 3]
He stood for dreams both big and small,
For every citizen, for one and all.
With steadfast heart and guiding hand,
He worked to elevate this land.

[Verse 4]
Some may debate, some may agree,
But history holds his legacy.
A leader's journey, bold and true,
Now etched where skies are vast and blue.

[Chorus]
When my dad is on Mount Rushmore,
His legacy forevermore.
Carved in stone, for all to see,
A testament to our country's legacy.
Through trials faced and battles won,
His story joins the timeless ones.
When my dad is on Mount Rushmore,
America's spirit will endure.

[Bridge]
So here's to visions that inspire,
To reaching higher and aiming higher.
A nation's gratitude displayed,
In granite heights that won't fade.

[Chorus]
When my dad is on Mount Rushmore,
His legacy forevermore.
Carved in stone, for all to see,
A testament to our country's legacy.
Through trials faced and battles won,
His story joins the timeless ones.
When my dad is on Mount Rushmore,
America's spirit will endure.

[Outro]
In the heart of the Black Hills' lore,
His image stands forevermore.
A tribute to the red, white, blue,
And to the dreams that we pursue.
